Bar plot:

I wanted to show if there is disproportion in number of congress members based on their gender

cel$party <- recode(cel$dem, `1` = "Democrats", `0` = "Republicans")
cel$gender <- recode(cel$female, `1` = "Female", `0` = "Male")

ggplot(cel, aes(x = party, fill = gender)) + geom_bar(position = "dodge2", width = 0.7) +
    labs(title = "Share of female and male congress members", x = NULL, y = "count",
        fill = NULL) + scale_fill_manual(values = c("#E82CE4", "#D9C1D0")) + theme_minimal() +
    theme(text = element_text(family = "Nunito SemiBold"), plot.title = element_text(face = "bold",
        size = 12), panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "black", size = 0.1,
        linetype = "dotted"), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), aspect.ratio = 1,
        legend.text = element_text(size = 8), legend.key.size = unit(0.8, "lines"),
        legend.box.spacing = unit(0.1, "cm"), axis.text.y = element_text(size = 7)) +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 6000))

Scatter plot:

I‚Äôve decided to stick with marginalized groups and visualize how many bills proposed by members with different levels of seniority became laws, grouping them by gender and ethnicity

cel$etni <- recode(cel$afam, `0` = "Other", `1` = "African American")
cel$membership <- recode(cel$dem, `0` = "Republican", `1` = "Democrat")

cel %>%
    filter(year >= 2010) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = seniority, y = all_law, color = membership)) + geom_point(position = "jitter",
    alpha = 1/2) + facet_wrap(gender ~ etni, labeller = label_wrap_gen(multi_line = FALSE)) +
    labs(x = "seniority", y = "bills transformed into laws", color = "Political Party") +
    scale_color_manual(values = c("#2C3AE8", "#E82CE4")) + theme_minimal() + theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 10, hjust = 1), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 10,
        hjust = 1), legend.position = "top", legend.title = element_blank(), legend.justification = c(-0.08,
        0), legend.margin = margin(0), aspect.ratio = 1) + ggtitle("relation of member seniority to bills passed ",
    subtitle = "by ethnicity and gender")

Line plot:

In Exercise 1 I was checking if there is a disproportion and now I want to examine its division by ethnicity

ex3dat <- cel %>%
    count(year, etni, gender)
annotation <- data.frame(ex3dat, lab = "disproportion between genders") %>%
    filter(etni == "Other")

ggplot(ex3dat, aes(x = year, y = n, color = gender)) + geom_line() + geom_text(data = annotation,
    aes(x = 1995, y = 200, label = lab), color = "black", check_overlap = TRUE) +
    facet_wrap(~etni) + labs(title = "Gender division in congress by ethnicity",
    x = "Year of observation", y = "Number of Indyviduals") + scale_color_manual(values = c("#E82CE4",
    "#2C3AE8")) + theme_bw() + theme(legend.title = element_blank())

Density plot:

Visualization of ideology distribution among congress members divided by ethnicity and gender after year 2000

caption <- paste(strwrap("Ideology distribution of congress members after year 2000",
    40), collapse = "\n")

cel %>%
    filter(year >= 2000) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = dwnom1, color = gender)) + geom_density() + annotate(geom = "text",
    x = 0, y = 3, label = caption, hjust = 0, size = 3) + facet_grid(etni ~ .) +
    labs(x = "ideology (higher = more conservative)", y = "density") + scale_color_manual(values = c("#E82CE4",
    "#D9C1D0")) + theme_minimal() + theme(panel.spacing = unit(1, "lines"), plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 10), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 10),
    legend.position = "right", legend.title = element_blank(), legend.box = "dot")
